   Dot And You a Winning Team


   DOT OSDBU Home

   Date item added: Thursday December 27, 2001

   DOT plans to hire a significant number of new Federal security
   screeners. Basic eligibility requirements have been published.

   Date item added: Thursday December 27, 2001

   The January 2002 Edition of the OSDBU newsletter, The Transportation
   Link, is now available on-line.

   Date item added: Tuesday December 18, 2001

   FAA Clears Santa for Christmas Flight! Press Release.

   Date item added: Tuesday December 18, 2001

   SBA launches BusinessLaw.gov, a new Web site designed to help reduce
   the burden of complying with laws and regulations. SBA press release.

   Date item added: Tuesday December 11, 2001

   The Questions and Answers pertaining to the Department of
   Transportation's (DOT) Disadvantaged Business Enterprise (DBE) program
   have been updated.

   Date item added: Thursday December 06, 2001

   The FAA is soliciting suggestions and recommendations to assist in the
   planning phase of their National Procurement Conference and Trade Show
   to be held on May 6-8, 2002.

   Date item added: Tuesday December 04, 2001

   DOT is hiring new Federal Security Screeners under the Transportation
   Security Act.

   Date item added: Friday November 30, 2001

   Secretary Mineta Announces Appointment of Sean M. Moss As Director of
   DOTs Small and Disadvantaged Business Office.

   Date item added: Friday November 30, 2001

   SBA Funds Grant Program for Very Small Businesses. SBA Press Release

   Date item added: Friday November 16, 2001

   December 2001 Edition of the OSDBU Newsletters Transportation Link, is
   now available on-line.

   Date item added: Tuesday November 13, 2001

   Operation ABC (America Buckles Children) Mobilization will be held
   November 19-25, 2001 as part of an effort to Keep America's Highways
   Safe. Buckle Up America!

   Date item added: Tuesday October 30, 2001

   November 2001 Edition of the Transportation Link is now available.

   Date item added: Thursday October 25, 2001

   Minority And Women Entrepreneurs Honored At DOT Awards Ceremony. Press
   Release.

   Date item added: Tuesday October 23, 2001

   The open period of the RSPA Broad Agency Announcement soliciting white
   papers on approaches to improve transportation infrastructure assurance
   (TIA) has been extended to November 21, 2001. Original press release.
   Contract announcements.

   Date item added: Friday October 19, 2001

   A Veterans Business Development Conference is being held on November
   13, 2001 in Fairmont, West Virginia.

   Date item added: Thursday October 04, 2001

   DOT's Research and Special Programs Administration (RSPA) is soliciting
   white papers on innovative transportation service and infrastructure
   assurance approaches which may lead to research project awards.

